        options={availableFinancingOptions}
        onChange={selectFinancingOption}
      />
      {isLeasing && <LeasingDetails />}
      <SurfaceConfigurator
        surfaces={surfaceConfiguration}
        onToggleSurface={actions.toggleSurface}
      />
    </div>
  );
}
```

This approach:
1. Uses SWR for data fetching and caching
2. Provides a clear interface for data and actions
3. Handles calculation polling automatically
4. Splits complex logic into focused hooks
5. Maintains type safety
6. Makes the data and actions easily accessible
7. Removes the need for complex reducers and context
8. Uses modern React patterns (hooks, memoization)

You can expand this further with additional helper hooks or utilities as needed, but this provides a solid foundation for managing interest state and actions in a modern React application.
